The Vigilante plugged

711
01:08:01,465 --> 01:08:03,693
his first victim in
Riverside Park...

712
01:08:03,830 --> 01:08:08,176
exactly two and one half blocks
from that D'Agostino market.

713
01:08:08,793 --> 01:08:12,843
Even if all these guys are clean,
we still can't ignore that coincidence.

714
01:08:13,339 --> 01:08:14,556
No, sir.

715
01:08:15,133 --> 01:08:17,261
Our friend lives in
that neighborhood.

716
01:08:17,427 --> 01:08:21,773
But, Frank, he was on a subway
with groceries five miles uptown.

717
01:08:22,599 --> 01:08:26,479
There's no better come-on for a mugging
than a guy with a bagful of groceries.

718
01:08:26,686 --> 01:08:30,361
Means he's got some money in his pocket
and his hands are occupied.

719
01:08:30,732 --> 01:08:33,906
He might have been carrying
those groceries for hours.

720
01:08:35,903 --> 01:08:38,281
I want a preliminary line
on these names.

721
01:08:38,448 --> 01:08:44,706
Where they work, service record,
reputation, police record, if any.

722
01:08:45,330 --> 01:08:48,504
And I want it fast.

723
01:08:49,125 --> 01:08:52,504
You know, like today, huh?

724
01:08:53,755 --> 01:08:57,134
It's probably having as much
effect on the total crime picture...

725
01:08:57,300 --> 01:08:59,177
as putting a
Band-Aid on a leper.

726
01:08:59,344 --> 01:09:01,425
Wait a minute, I
don't know about that,

727
01:09:01,451 --> 01:09:03,670
a mugger's gonna think
twice about who he hits.

728
01:09:03,806 --> 01:09:06,025
Sure. They're hitting more
old ladies, that's why.

729
01:09:06,184 --> 01:09:08,858
Paul, how you doing?
Let me get you a drink.

730
01:09:11,606 --> 01:09:13,404
The guy's a racist.

731
01:09:13,608 --> 01:09:15,406
You notice he kills
more blacks than whites.

732
01:09:15,568 --> 01:09:17,946
Oh, for Pete's sake, more blacks
are muggers than whites.

733
01:09:18,112 --> 01:09:20,865
What do you want us to do, increase
the proportion of white muggers...

734
01:09:21,032 --> 01:09:22,875
so we'll have racial equality
among muggers?

735
01:09:23,034 --> 01:09:26,459
Racial equality among muggers?
Ooh. I love it!

736
01:09:26,663 --> 01:09:28,711
He hasn't been the same
since that terrible incident.

737
01:10:03,783 --> 01:10:08,584
- Who we got here?
- A guy named Paul... Kersey.

738
01:10:08,788 --> 01:10:10,711
His wife was murdered
in their apartment.

739
01:10:10,873 --> 01:10:13,626
Interesting detail:
The attackers, three of them...

740
01:10:13,835 --> 01:10:16,384
gained entrance to the apartment
by posing as delivery boys...

741
01:10:16,546 --> 01:10:20,267
from our D'Agostino's market, where
The Vigilante buys his groceries.

742
01:10:20,967 --> 01:10:22,093
What else about him?

743
01:10:22,719 --> 01:10:24,312
He lives alone now.

744
01:10:24,512 --> 01:10:27,732
Development engineer
for the Blue Ridge corporation.

745
01:10:27,974 --> 01:10:30,022
Served in Korea, medical corps.

746
01:10:30,601 --> 01:10:32,444
Conscientious objector.

747
01:10:32,603 --> 01:10:36,608
No police record.
Credits, reputation excellent.

748
01:10:37,316 --> 01:10:40,115
Conscientious objectors
are unlikely vigilantes.

749
01:10:40,903 --> 01:10:44,032
- We got a finger?
- Yeah. Over there.

750
01:10:44,240 --> 01:10:47,335
Patrolman Joe Charles.

751
01:10:47,493 --> 01:10:48,665
Good.

752
01:10:52,749 --> 01:10:54,126
Good morning, Mr. Kersey.

753
01:10:54,876 --> 01:10:56,423
Joe Charles, Mr. Kersey.

754
01:10:56,627 --> 01:10:58,174
Oh, yes, of course.

755
01:10:58,337 --> 01:11:00,385
How do you do?
Good to see you again.

756
01:11:00,590 --> 01:11:02,183
How's your daughter?

757
01:11:02,759 --> 01:11:04,227
The same.

758
01:11:04,761 --> 01:11:06,308
Take care.

759
01:11:09,557 --> 01:11:11,025
Follow him.

760
01:11:23,863 --> 01:11:25,661
Yes, I'll see to that, Mrs. Cohen.

761
01:11:28,701 --> 01:11:30,954
Just a moment.
You're not residents here.

762
01:11:31,162 --> 01:11:32,914
Who do you wish to see?
I'll call up for you.

763
01:11:33,080 --> 01:11:34,423
No, you won't.

764
01:13:18,811 --> 01:13:21,189
The district
attorney will see you now.

765
01:13:30,948 --> 01:13:33,827
- Commissioner.
- Frank, you know the district attorney.

766
01:13:34,952 --> 01:13:37,375
- Mr. Peters.
- Inspector.

767
01:13:38,789 --> 01:13:41,383
The commissioner says you
have a pretty good suspect.

768
01:13:41,834 --> 01:13:45,384
Well, he fits the bill
in some respects.

769
01:13:45,838 --> 01:13:49,012
We got a blood sample
from the knife...

770
01:13:49,175 --> 01:13:52,520
used on him in the subway and
checked it against the sample...

771
01:13:52,678 --> 01:13:54,305
I found in his apartment.

772
01:13:55,181 --> 01:13:56,478
It narrows it down.

773
01:13:56,724 --> 01:13:58,726
But in the balance,
he could be the man?

774
01:13:59,185 --> 01:14:00,357
Yeah.

775
01:14:00,937 --> 01:14:02,735
Yeah, he could be.

776
01:14:03,397 --> 01:14:04,740
Frank...

777
01:14:06,108 --> 01:14:09,408
Suppose this Paul Kersey
is The Vigilante.

778
01:14:09,946 --> 01:14:11,914
All right. Let's say that.

779
01:14:14,825 --> 01:14:16,042
We don't want him.

780
01:14:18,537 --> 01:14:19,914
Okay.

781
01:14:20,081 --> 01:14:24,837
Inspector, on my desk, I have a statistic
red-hot out of the computer.

782
01:14:25,044 --> 01:14:26,091
Mm-hm.

783
01:14:26,253 --> 01:14:29,302
Mugging has gone down
by how much, sir?

784
01:14:29,840 --> 01:14:33,765
From 950 a week
to 470 reported last week.

785
01:14:33,928 --> 01:14:35,930
You understand
not too many people know that.

786
01:14:36,639 --> 01:14:39,358
And you wanna keep
it that way, huh?

787
01:14:39,517 --> 01:14:42,020
Oh, no, we have to keep it
that way, inspector.

788
01:14:42,979 --> 01:14:44,731
This whole city would explode.

789
01:14:44,939 --> 01:14:48,819
We'd have vigilantes out in the street
killing anybody who even looked greasy.

790
01:14:49,360 --> 01:14:53,115
- You can see that.
- We want this man to quit, desist...

791
01:14:53,614 --> 01:14:56,834
go away.
To stop.

792
01:14:59,328 --> 01:15:01,422
So the mugging rate can go up?

793
01:15:03,124 --> 01:15:05,377
If I arrest him, wouldn't that
get him off the streets?

794
01:15:05,543 --> 01:15:07,841
My God, man. I don't want
a martyr on my hands.

795
01:15:08,004 --> 01:15:11,349
All right.
All right.

796
01:15:11,882 --> 01:15:14,055
I just wanna hear you say it.

797
01:15:20,099 --> 01:15:21,851
I'll try to scare him off...

798
01:15:22,560 --> 01:15:24,654
but that's as far as I'll go.

799
01:15:24,854 --> 01:15:28,233
That's right, Frank.
Scare him off.

800
01:15:30,109 --> 01:15:31,907
Scare him off?

801
01:15:45,958 --> 01:15:47,005
Yes?

802
01:15:47,168 --> 01:15:49,842
<i>A call for you from a man
who says he's an old friend...</i>

803
01:15:50,004 --> 01:15:51,756
<i>and wonders if you'll
recognize his voice.</i>

804
01:15:51,964 --> 01:15:55,013
Do you want the call that way,
or shall I insist upon his name?

805
01:15:55,468 --> 01:15:58,187
- Okay, I'll take it.
- <i>I'm putting you through.</i>

806
01:16:00,931 --> 01:16:03,684
- Hello?
- Is this Paul Kersey?

807
01:16:03,893 --> 01:16:05,566
Yes. Who's this?

808
01:16:07,521 --> 01:16:10,570
Mr. Kersey, you're under
police surveillance.

809
01:16:11,025 --> 01:16:13,119
<i>You're being watched.</i>

810
01:16:21,494 --> 01:16:24,668
Scare him off.
Heh. Ha-ha-ha.

811
01:16:36,342 --> 01:16:39,141
Papers! Papers!

812
01:16:39,470 --> 01:16:42,474
Read all about The Vigilante!

813
01:16:43,099 --> 01:16:45,352
Get your papers here!

814
01:16:45,518 --> 01:16:47,816
Read all about The Vigilante!

815
01:16:48,187 --> 01:16:49,939
How are you this evening, sir?

816
01:16:50,106 --> 01:16:52,655
Papers! Papers!

817
01:16:52,817 --> 01:16:55,240
Read all about The Vigilante!

818
01:17:11,752 --> 01:17:13,817
All right, you.
Get your hands up.

819
01:17:13,843 --> 01:17:15,532
Come on. Hands on the car.
Come on.

820
01:17:15,714 --> 01:17:17,136
Spread your legs.

821
01:17:25,516 --> 01:17:26,984
Okay. Turn around.

822
01:17:27,768 --> 01:17:29,816
Let's see some identification.

823
01:17:35,276 --> 01:17:38,450
- Where do you live?
- 33 Riverside.

824
01:17:38,737 --> 01:17:41,206
Okay, Mr. Kersey. Sorry to have
roughed you up so much.

825
01:17:41,365 --> 01:17:43,618
We're looking for a guy
pretty close to your description.

826
01:17:43,826 --> 01:17:48,081
He's supposed to be armed, and we couldn't
take any chances. I hope you understand.

827
01:17:49,373 --> 01:17:52,126
Look, if you wanna make a complaint,
I'll give you my number.

828
01:17:52,376 --> 01:17:53,923
It's all right.
Nobody was hurt.

829
01:17:54,128 --> 01:17:56,847
- Okay, thanks. Good night, Mr. Kersey.
- Night.

830
01:18:03,137 --> 01:18:04,389
Okay?

831
01:18:04,972 --> 01:18:06,064
Yeah.

832
01:18:06,932 --> 01:18:08,229
Okay.

833
01:18:28,871 --> 01:18:30,965
Went in the building
about 10 minutes ago.

834
01:18:31,123 --> 01:18:33,467
Went to D'Agostino's market first.

835
01:19:33,560 --> 01:19:35,153
Let's check him, huh?

836
01:19:36,438 --> 01:19:38,691
Go to that phone booth on
the corner, call his number.

837
01:19:38,857 --> 01:19:40,359
He's up there.

838
01:19:40,776 --> 01:19:42,403
Check him anyway.

839
01:20:56,977 --> 01:20:59,651
- Police! I need the phone.
- Come on!

840
01:21:00,356 --> 01:21:02,404
- Who is this guy?
- He must be crazy.

841
01:21:02,566 --> 01:21:04,614
He said "police."
I didn't see a badge.

842
01:21:11,283 --> 01:21:14,002
I'll call them. I'll call as soon
as he gets off the phone.

843
01:21:14,161 --> 01:21:17,085
- Thanks, pal.
- Yeah? Up yours!

844
01:21:23,629 --> 01:21:26,382
No answer. He could be
in the shower or something.

845
01:21:26,548 --> 01:21:28,050
Stay here.

846
01:22:24,314 --> 01:22:26,487
- Good night, Mr. Kersey.
- Good night.

847
01:22:55,429 --> 01:22:57,602
I'm supposed to meet Paul Kersey.
Has he gone up yet?

848
01:22:57,764 --> 01:23:01,610
Kersey? Yes, sir. He went up and
came down. Just walked out.

849
01:23:32,049 --> 01:23:35,098
- Where'd you go?
- He didn't show here, did he?

850
01:23:35,302 --> 01:23:36,975
Can I ask a simple question?

851
01:23:37,179 --> 01:23:39,398
Is this Paul Kersey the bird?

852
01:23:40,849 --> 01:23:42,943
I ain't gonna ask
any more questions.

853
01:23:43,227 --> 01:23:45,275
Go home, will you?
I don't need you.

854
01:23:45,437 --> 01:23:46,814
Weird!

855
01:24:16,718 --> 01:24:20,473
Come on down, motherfucker.
We gonna take you.

856
01:24:20,681 --> 01:24:24,857
That's right, motherfucker,
and you can't go back up, either.

857
01:24:32,776 --> 01:24:35,700
Come on down and bring
us the money, honey.

858
01:24:35,946 --> 01:24:38,665
How much money you got, honey?

859
01:24:44,580 --> 01:24:46,048
What the fuck?

860
01:24:47,040 --> 01:24:48,667
Fuck!

861
01:25:22,909 --> 01:25:24,877
<i>Units in the 2-6 precinct.</i>

862
01:25:25,037 --> 01:25:28,541
<i>A 10-34, 1-2-5 Street
and the West Side Highway.</i>

863
01:26:43,198 --> 01:26:44,495
Hey!

864
01:26:51,456 --> 01:26:52,548
Fill your hand.

865
01:26:53,834 --> 01:26:55,256
Huh?

866
01:26:58,463 --> 01:27:00,010
Draw.

867
01:27:42,758 --> 01:27:44,260
Where is he, this patrolman?

868
01:28:00,609 --> 01:28:02,031
- You're Reilly?
- Yes, sir.

869
01:28:02,194 --> 01:28:03,787
- I'm Ochoa.
- Yes, sir.

870
01:28:05,947 --> 01:28:08,075
- You were the first man on the scene?
- Yes, sir.

871
01:28:09,493 --> 01:28:12,372
- God bless you, sir.
- Never mind that.

872
01:28:14,206 --> 01:28:16,629
They told me on the radio
you had to see me?

873
01:28:16,917 --> 01:28:18,419
Paul Kersey.

874
01:28:19,795 --> 01:28:21,718
You spoke to him
before the ambulance got here?

875
01:28:21,922 --> 01:28:23,014
No, sir.

876
01:28:23,965 --> 01:28:25,763
- What did you get?
- His address, sir.

877
01:28:27,552 --> 01:28:28,929
Is that all?

878
01:28:31,389 --> 01:28:32,436
Well?

879
01:28:42,108 --> 01:28:43,860
You enter this on your report?

880
01:28:44,277 --> 01:28:45,324
Not yet, sir.

881
01:28:47,447 --> 01:28:48,539
Why not?

882
01:28:49,449 --> 01:28:50,746
I was, uh...

883
01:28:50,909 --> 01:28:52,536
waiting for instructions, sir.

884
01:28:53,328 --> 01:28:54,580
You never saw it.

885
01:28:56,581 --> 01:28:57,833
Yes, sir.

886
01:29:01,127 --> 01:29:03,971
Oh, uh... What's your full name?

887
01:29:04,172 --> 01:29:06,800
Jackson Reilly, sir.
21st precinct.

888
01:29:07,884 --> 01:29:10,888
Okay. I'll remember it.

889
01:29:23,650 --> 01:29:26,449
Inspector, is it true
that you have The Vigilante in there?

890
01:29:26,653 --> 01:29:28,747
- No.
- Well, who have you got there?

891
01:29:33,410 --> 01:29:35,458
Are you in charge? How is he?

892
01:29:35,620 --> 01:29:39,341
Wounds are clean. Nothing vital.
We have a transfusion going on now.

893
01:29:39,499 --> 01:29:41,718
Soon as we get some blood in him,
we'll sew him up again.

894
01:29:41,877 --> 01:29:42,924
- Is he in there?
- Yeah.

895
01:29:43,086 --> 01:29:45,214
- All right if I go in?
- He won't be able to talk much.

896
01:29:45,380 --> 01:29:48,054
- Can he hear me?
- He is conscious.

897
01:29:59,144 --> 01:30:01,863
Police. I'd like to have him alone.

898
01:30:17,037 --> 01:30:19,039
Good evening, Mr. Kersey.

899
01:30:25,337 --> 01:30:27,305
This is your gun, Mr. Kersey.

900
01:30:29,549 --> 01:30:31,847
We tried to give you a
chance to get rid of it.

901
01:30:32,177 --> 01:30:33,349
You wouldn't take it.

902
01:30:34,804 --> 01:30:36,727
Do you hear me okay?

903
01:30:38,350 --> 01:30:42,071
We have here a peculiar situation,
Mr. Kersey.

904
01:30:42,604 --> 01:30:45,480
We find it necessary to
make you a proposition

905
01:30:45,506 --> 01:30:48,136
since you are not gonna
favor us by dying.

906
01:30:49,152 --> 01:30:53,328
You work for a company
with lots of offices.

907
01:30:54,407 --> 01:30:57,001
Get a transfer to another city...

908
01:30:57,661 --> 01:30:59,880
and I'll drop this
gun in the river.

909
01:31:03,959 --> 01:31:08,214
Are we connecting, Mr. Kersey?

910
01:31:10,090 --> 01:31:12,559
We want you to get
out of New York.

911
01:31:13,259 --> 01:31:15,136
Permanently.

912
01:31:20,350 --> 01:31:21,727
Inspector.

913
01:31:25,814 --> 01:31:27,532
By sundown?

914
01:31:43,623 --> 01:31:44,875
- There he is.
- Here he comes.

915
01:31:45,083 --> 01:31:46,630
Do you have The Vigilante, inspector?

916
01:31:46,835 --> 01:31:49,463
- Can you give us information?
- No!

917
01:31:49,671 --> 01:31:51,344
Isn't the wounded man
The Vigilante?

918
01:31:51,548 --> 01:31:53,016
No. He's just a mugging victim.

919
01:31:53,216 --> 01:31:56,186
How do you explain the first
reports that he is The Vigilante?

920
01:31:56,344 --> 01:31:58,392
False reports.
It happens all the time.

921
01:31:58,596 --> 01:32:00,598
Then The Vigilante's
still out there?

922
01:32:00,765 --> 01:32:02,767
That's right. He's still
out there on the streets.

923
01:32:02,976 --> 01:32:06,025
- Let me through.
- Was he shot by The Vigilante?

924
01:32:17,615 --> 01:32:21,165
<i>The Amtrak train from New York to
Chicago has arrived on Track 8.</i>

925
01:32:22,537 --> 01:32:24,255
- Mr. Kersey.
- Paul Kersey.

926
01:32:24,414 --> 01:32:27,338
Fred Brown. Welcome to Chicago, sir.
Did you have a nice trip?

927
01:32:27,500 --> 01:32:28,626
Yeah, it was okay.

928
01:32:28,793 --> 01:32:30,481
Good. I found a nice
apartment for you.

929
01:32:30,507 --> 01:32:32,448
I hope you like it. It's
on Lake Shore Drive.

930
01:32:32,589 --> 01:32:36,139
You have a view of Lake Michigan, morning
sun. We've got your office ready too.

931
01:32:36,342 --> 01:32:38,060
There's a very good
golf club, if you play.

932
01:32:39,012 --> 01:32:41,856
- Listen, I think you'll enjoy it here.
- Excuse me.
